title: Meta issues purge date for Australian teens' accounts ahead of govt ban | ABC NEWS
description: Meta has put Australian teens on notice with direct warnings that under 16s are about to be kicked off some social media platforms. The government's social media minimum age law comes into force on December 10, but the tech giant is taking early action. title: Investor relief as Nvidia's results calm fears of an AI bubble | The Business | ABC NEWS
description: The world's most valuable company, Nvidia has delivered an impressive result, lifting the gloom around stretched valuations on markets for now, as investors look past concerns about AI spending. The tech darling announced year-on-year revenue growth of 62 per cent to $US57 billion in the third quarter, exceeding expectations of $US54.9 billion. VanEck cross-asset specialist, Anna Wu told The Business, "Blackwell chips sales remain strong, a reflection of demand for high-end chips".    The company forecast $US65 billion in revenue for the current quarter. Anna Wu says the bar to impress investors is now set very high.  She says almost all cloud providers are customers of Nvidia and its growing to be one of the largest cash-rich investors in the industry. But the big question now is whether all this AI capacity being built today will become profitable in the future. #ABCBusiness Subscribe: http://ab.co/1svxLVE  ABC NEWS provides around the clock coverage of news events as they break in Australia and abroad. title: Australia hands COP31 to Türkiye, though Chris Bowen to lead talks | ABC NEWS
description: Australia has bowed out of the race to host the world's largest climate change meeting, instead striking a deal with Türkiye. It's a blow for Adelaide, the city that was set to host, and climate advocates who wanted to use the summit to drive climate action. The government says it had to compromise to break the diplomatic impasse. As a condition of the agreement, Australian Climate Minister Chris Bowen will lead negotiations at the summit. title: China bans seafood from Japan, calls on PM Takaichi to retract Taiwan remarks | The World | ABC News
description: Beijing has upped the ante on its diplomatic dispute with Tokyo - suspending all seafood imports form Japan. China says the move was prompted by the need to further monitor the water from Fukushima being released in the ocean. But it's being viewed as another act of retaliation by Beijing over Prime Minister Sanae Takaichi's recent remarks about triggering a military response if China invades Taiwan. title: Dozens killed in Russian strike on apartment buildings in west Ukraine | The World | ABC NEWS
description: The western Ukrainian city of Ternopil has been hit by a major Russian drone attack that killed 25 people, including several children. It comes as Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy travels to Turkiye as part of efforts to increase international pressure on Vladimir Putin. Meanwhile, a Russian spy ship has been spotted near British territory, as Moscow continues to test the boundaries of NATO and its allies. Global affairs analyst Michael Bociurkiw tells The World it's been an "unbelievable" 48 hours.
